      <h1>Chord Theory</h1>
      <p>
      The table below lists the different types of chords that are possible in music and how to construct them.       <br/>
      The table shows which notes of the major scale are needed to build each chord type and provides an corresponding<br/>
      example based on the C major scale.
      </p>
      <p>
      Note that the symbol for flat "b" can also be written as a minus sign "-", and the symbol for sharp "#" can similarly be written with a plus sign, "+".
